Nutritional analysis provided by Self", 'recommendation': u'85%', 'ingredient list': [u'1 tablespoon olive oil', u'2 cloves garlic, sliced', u'Red pepper flakes', u'1/2 cup dry white wine', u'12 Manila or littleneck clams', u'10 ounces linguine', u'3/4 cup tomato sauce', u'12 black mussels', u'8 shrimp, shelled (tail intact) and deveined', u'4 sea scallops, quartered', u'5 ounces calamari, cut into thin rings', u'1/4 cup fresh flat-leaf parsley, coarsely chopped'], 'preperation steps': [u'Boil water in a large pot. Heat oil in a large saut\xe9 pan over medium heat. Cook garlic until it sizzles. Add red pepper flakes to taste; cook 1 minute. Add wine and clams; cover. Raise heat to medium-high; cook 5 minutes. Add linguine to boiling water. Cook until al dente. Uncover saut\xe9 pan; simmer 1 minute more. Add tomato sauce. Season with salt and pepper. Add rest of seafood. Cook, stirring, until clams and mussels open, about 3 minutes. Toss with linguine. Add parsley; toss. Divide among 4 bowls.'], 'chef': u'pted by Lesley Porcelli', 'r_link': '/recipes/food/views/linguine-ai-frutti-di-mare-238646', 'prep_time': None, 'servings': u'Makes 4 servings', 'recipe title': u'Linguine ai Frutti di Mare', 'image_source': '/static/img/px/background.png'}

