Nutritional analysis provided by Nutrition Data", 'recommendation': u'83%', 'ingredient list': [u'6 small to medium zucchini (about 1 1/2 pounds total), trimmed', u'1 large cucumber (about 13 ounces), peeled, seeded, diced', u'1 cup finely chopped Vidalia or Maui onion', u'1 1/2 cups (loosely packed) fresh mint leaves, coarsely chopped, divided', u'2 teaspoons finely grated lemon peel', u'4 tablespoons fresh lemon juice', u'2 tablespoons pistachio oil'], 'preperation steps': [u'Using mandoline or V-slicer and working with 1 zucchini at a time, thinly slice lengthwise, discarding first strip. Slice up to seeded core; turn zucchini and continue to slice until only rectangle of seeded core remains; discard core. Place slices in medium bowl.', u'Add cucumber, onion, 1/2 of chopped mint, and lemon peel. Whisk lemon juice and pistachio oil in small bowl, then pour over zucchini mixture; toss to coat. Season with salt and generously with pepper. Cover zucchini mixture and refrigerate at least 1 hour and up to 3 hours.', u'Sprinkle remaining chopped mint over salad and toss to coat.'], 'chef': u'Dorie Greenspan', 'r_link': '/recipes/food/views/zucchini-tagliatelle-with-mint-cucumber-and-lemon-242986', 'prep_time': None, 'servings': u'Makes 6 servings', 'recipe title': u'Zucchini "Tagliatelle" with Mint, Cucumber, and Lemon', 'image_source': None}
